Step 1. Operating Cash Flow Ratio 
• Formula: Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities 
• From the cash‐flow statement, Operating Cash Flow = –1,919,526.63 
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 5,637,910.70 
• Ratio = –1,919,526.63 / 5,637,910.70 ≈ –0.3406, which rounded to two decimals is –0.34

Step 2. Cash Flow to Debt Ratio 
• This ratio is defined similarly here as Operating Cash Flow divided by Total Debt – in this context Total Debt is taken as Total Current Liabilities. 
• Thus, it also equals –1,919,526.63 / 5,637,910.70 ≈ –0.34

Step 3. Inventory Turnover Ratio 
• We use the Average Inventory since the beginning balance is 0. 
• Average Inventory = (0 + 7,446,940.00) / 2 = 3,723,470.00 
• From the income statement, Cost of Goods Sold = 544,970.00 
• Inventory Turnover = 544,970.00 / 3,723,470.00 ≈ 0.1464, which rounds to 0.15

Step 4. Debt to Equity Ratio 
• Formula: Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity 
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities (our debt) = 5,637,910.70 
• Total Owner’s Equity = 16,099,532.29 
• Ratio = 5,637,910.70 / 16,099,532.29 ≈ 0.350, or 0.35

Step 5. Quick Ratio 
• Formula: Quick Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits + Interest Receivable + Accounts Receivable) / Total Current Liabilities 
• Add the quick assets: 
 Cash on Hand = 2,105,753.37 
 Bank Deposits = 559,055.66 
 Interest Receivable = 6,494.02 
 Accounts Receivable = 335,639.38 
• Sum = 2,105,753.37 + 559,055.66 + 6,494.02 + 335,639.38 = 3,006,942.43 
• Quick Ratio = 3,006,942.43 / 5,637,910.70 ≈ 0.5338, which is about 0.53

Step 6. Current Ratio 
• Formula: Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities 
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Assets = 10,453,882.43 
• Total Current Liabilities = 5,637,910.70 
• Ratio = 10,453,882.43 / 5,637,910.70 ≈ 1.854, or 1.85

Thus, the final results in the required format are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.34",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-0.34",
    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "0.15",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.35",
    "Quick Ratio": "0.53",
    "Current Ratio": "1.85"
  }
}
